message: Hello.
Thanks, Joe! But what are you doing here?
What do the wizards say??
It's OK.
I'm not interested.
I'd like to get to island CX. Can you take me there?
I'd like to buy some gazogem.
I'm trying to get to island CX.
Are you winning?
What should I do?
It's OK!
But Jerome, I've got to find island CX and destroy the machines that control the lunar reactors!
I don't care about that.
The island of the Francos.
Celebration Island.
I'd like to see Rick, the boss.
You know Rick, I'd like to see him.

The emperor had some secret base built on island CX. From there, he'll trigger the firing of these reactors built on the moon in utmost secrecy which'll destroy my whole planet. I've got to go to this island to prevent this from happening. Could you help me get there?
I'm looking for a Mr. Johnny Rocket.
Are you Mr. Rocket?
I'm here on behalf of Rick to look for the dissidents, and I desperately need to get to island CX!
Not yet.
That's me. I have to get to island CX and somehow destroy the control center of the lunar reactors before they're fired and the moon starts falling toward Twinsun.
Where should I go?
I'm staying here.
I don't have enough Kashes.
I don't have enough Zlitos.
"You are at the harbor of Otringal."
"You are in downtown Otringal."
"You are at the astroport of Otringal."
"THE ZEELICH GAZETTE: ...Johnny Rocket at the Imperial! Zeelich's brightest star, the first explorer to set foot on Twinsun, now lives on Otringal..."
"THE INQUIRER : ...group of dissidents who defaced our beautiful city with subversive posters.... some will be arrested... the police are looking for runaways..."
"OTRINGAL NEWS : The twinsunian wizards on a visit of Otringal..."
"THE OFFICIAL RUMOR: The Emperor asserts: Dark Monk will fulfill the prophecy, whether or not the mosquibees are willing to bring their fragment!!!"
"THE DESPATCH OF ZEELICH: shortage of gazogem, the tankers stopped supplying Otringal!"
"THE INQUIRER: Looking for witnesses! 10,000 Zlitos reward!!! If you see a Twinsunian in a blue tunic, call the police immediately...armed and dangerous..."
"OTRINGAL NEWS: Twinsunian Anarchist Disrupts Dark Monk's Ceremony...
"THE OFFICIAL RUMOR: Emperor Reveals: Dark Monk Warned Me! He predicted a Twinsunian dressed in blue would try to prevent our ceremony..."
"2:55 p.m., shuttle 65 38, destination planet Zirla for fly safari... 3:20 p.m., shuttle 007, destination red planet..."

"WANTED: The so-called "Twinsen." Master criminal - Trying to oppose Dark Monk and prevent the great celebration - Wears blue tunic - If you see him, call the police - Anyone helping bring this miscreant into custody will be rewarded the amount of 10,000 Zlitos."
I hold a wizard's diploma.
One ferry ticket.
I have an umbrella.
I've got some Twinsunian money.
I already have a crystal, so now I'll be able to use this laser pistol.
But... who do you mean?

This painting is strange, signed by some guy...Gramitte.

Whoah, these paintings are bogus!
This control panel's been modified. Apparently, I can't put the itinerary tokens in here anymore.
There's a piece missing, something disc-shaped. I guess I need it for the shuttle to take off.
Depiction of Zeelich, the Planet of a Thousand Wonders!!

Welcome to Zeelich, Master. Follow me, I will take you to your twinsunian colleagues.
Follow us!!

Watch the hair!!
Here we are, Master, on our way to Zeelich! Relax, the trip will not be very long.
You are welcome, Master. Make yourself comfortable.
But... it's... Twinsen! Yo, Twinsen! It's me, Joe the Elf! Your old friend! Good to see you again!!!

Hey, Twinsen, great bumping into you! Say, you don't seem all that buddy-buddy with the locals! Soon as they heard your name, they jumped you, knocked you out, and stole your wizard's costume. And now, we're in jail.

Actually I was with the wizards when the Esmers invited them to this planet. Now, they're being held captive by the emperor and claim the Esmers want to kidnap the children of Twinsun. I got scared, so I left, and found you there.

They say the Esmers left for our planet to kidnap Twinsun's children! They say nothing can be done, but I still have hope. I'm sure you will succeed in reaching the astroport to steal a shuttle and go save those children!!!
Ah, not so nice, that one. I'd rather not be left alone with him!!

Welcome to Zeelich, the planet of a thousand wonders!!

Its beauty will dazzle your eyes. The kindness of its inhabitants will warm your heart!

We are the craftsmen of your happiness.

Have trust in our friendship!!

In our laboratories, our scientists are developing a technology of the future, capable of crossing space to come meet you personally.

Come! Come share our science.

If you don't meet with him, you might at least get a glance of our most high Emperor.

With an unequaled kindness, he oversees our planet with skill and leniency.

At the palace doors, you will get a look at his personal guard.

They are imperial warriors, who perform a majestic parade every day.
After that, you will try your luck in one of our extraordinary casinos, where you might win the "Total Jackpot"!!

And don't forget to get a taste of our culinary specialties.

Feel free to help yourself to a second slice of our unique firefly tart!!
And, to crown your evening, you can learn our local dances in one of our prestigious clubs!!

By no means!

You shouldn't leave Zeelich without witnessing the unique, the incomparable, the one and only ceremony of Dark Monk, our all powerful God!!!

Emerging from the crater of the volcano, amid a shimmer of lava explosions, his statue will inscribe the Redemption of our people in letters of fire!

Only then will you leave Zeelich, your head filled with images and your heart ablaze with zest for life.

Meanwhile, and awaiting your visit here, we thank you for your kind attention to our modest presentation.
Insert 10 Zlitos if you want 10 Magic points

I've had it with these Zeelichians!! They're totally nuts. Cops combing the streets, Cops everywhere, soon as we do a little something the wrong way, they jump all over us! I'm getting fed up with this conditional freedom!
I'm leaving for Zirla. Heard they organize fantastic safaris, but I don't see the actual organizers anywhere. Hope I didn't pick the wrong day.
Twinsen, I damaged the vessel during landing. I need some time for repairs. The Zeelichian fuel is called gazogem, it's very powerful. You should go get some.
Of course, but I will need this gazogem sooner or later. Besides, it will allow me to transform your protopack and increase its performance.
You must go get me some gazogem, so that I can finish to repair our vessel and make your protopack more powerful!!
Thanks, Twinsen. Now I can finish up on the ship. I'll buzz you on the radio as soon as I do the protopack.
Hey there, don't forget my gazogem. I really need it to repair the vessel. And I think you'll really appreciate what it does to your protopack.
Thank you, Twinsen. Now I can make us a ship that can race the comets! Anyway, here's something to turn your protopack into a superjetpack. and from now on, you can fly higher!
It's going to take me quite a while longer to finish up on the vessel here.
Come in! Twinsen? It's me, Baldino! I've improved your protopack, you can come pick it up now!
On island CX? No way Jack! That's rough turf over there!!
For 5 Zlitos, I can take you somewheres. Where do you wanna go?
Oh most certainly not, sir. For some time now, nobody is returning from there. They say a monster is lurking in the area. No one in their right mind will take you there!
For 5 Zlitos, I can be taking you somewhere. Where do you want to go sir?
Hmmm... Maybe yes, maybe no, maybe both... Might be able to tell you something about it... expensive, though... maybe 100 Zlitos... and maybe 'cause it's you...
I do know a dude who came back. These days, he sells souvenirs on Celebration Island. Might be able to take you to him.... Oh well, for you, it's a freebie! Welcome aboard Leontine, my cab!!
If you want, mate, you can climb aboard my Leontine and I'll take you someplace for 10 Zlitos. OK then? Where to?
Hello sir. I might be able to help you.
Listen, mac. Do what you want, but don't give us trouble! Otherwise Riri and Momo'll twist you into a pretzel and dip you in hot cider! That's how we handle your type around here. You dig?
The boss don't see nobody.
Why not just enjoy the show instead of fretting like that.
Hello sir.
Hey, buddy, you lost something? What is it? You looking for your glasses? Here, we'll help you out!
the Boss no touch!
No touch the Boss!
Hello sir.
Hey get lost man!!
You're on!
Lousy audience. They used to be so cool! And they came by the thousands!!!
Island CX? You got to be kidding? Lots of guys tried to get there, but not one ever came back. I'd be surprised if you get someone to ferry you over.
Yeah, I see who it is. A bit of free advice: don't try to reach him. Not only is he highly respected and inaccessible, but this is his home turf. Just drop it!

Hmmm, aren't you the one the police are after? I heard you want to stop Dark Monk from celebrating the last ceremony, the one that'll rid us of the curse. Please don't screw it up, we've been waiting for a millennia.

Hmmm... Nobody wants to go there these days, it's way too risky. They say monsters have come out of the gas over there. Try the Captain, he's the old nut at the very end of the pier. He's the only one who'd take you!
Hmmm, you look a lot like the one all the cops are after. You'll be fine here but watch your back if you wander away from this little area.
I ain't takin' you noplace. Go try the casino Gloum. If you win the Jackpot, you'll have a nice surprise.
Go try your luck at the casino Gloum. I've been there, there is always a surprise waiting for you!
So, you are the notorious Twinsunian who's dying to see me. You're on the run, my friend, the police are all after you. Impressive. So spit it out, what do you want?

I'll level with you. Unfortunately, I have no one who can accommodate your needs. But there's a group of dissidents who are very hostile to the government. Go see Johnny Rocket. Tell him Rick sent you, and he'll take you to them. He lives at the Imperial hotel, in the upper city.
He's our greatest hero. The first one to set foot on mysterious Twinsun! Thanks to him we'll get much-needed help from the Twinsunian wizards! He's over there, in the armchair, with his manicurist.
I adore this hotel. Kind of a private club. Only the finest elements of society are allowed entry.
I've had it with this lousy joint! I'm moving on! The Imperial hotel, that's where I should have been all this time! Nothing but classy people there, not a bunch of unwashed hoodlums or sailors.
Get lost!
I can't wait for my shift to be over, I got to go buy some gazogem at the service station of Otringal.
Hello, sir, and welcome to Gambling Paradise!
You can try your luck at the gaming tables or the slots. It's your choice.
If you want sir, I can have you taken back up to the exit of the casino.
Ah, my dear sir, the Lady Luck is a fickle female! I have been losing since the curse of Dark Monk condemned us to live forever on this miserable planet. But the day will come when I will win!
To play, stand in front of a marker or a machine, and insert some Zlitos. If you play the slots, you could win the super Jackpot of the evening. It will grant you admission to our special room!
Wait a minute, I smell a rat! I am sure that this filthy critter has been trained.
You cheater!!
Come on Baby...
Yippee!!!!
Stand in front of one of the four markers, and place your bets.

Welcome, my dear sir! Welcome, welcome to our wheel of fortune! So you're the one fate has chosen today to try for our Super Jackpot! Excellent, excellent. Now, just stand behind the wheel on the small podium, give it a whirl, and maybe, maybe I say, you will hit it big!!!
It's very simple, my friend. Stand on the small podium, and give the wheel a good hard spin!
Banzai!
Stand in front of the article of your choice and do "ACTION" if you want to buy it.
I couldn't help but notice you're from Twinsun. Would you be interested in selling me anything from your planet? Something little-bitty, even?
Downstairs you'll find the rest of the dissidents waiting for you. Johnny has told us you are coming.
Go, they're downstairs.
20 Life points cost 20 Zlitos.
20 Magic points cost 20 Zlitos.
One meca-penguin costs 15 Zlitos.
I'll buy it from you for 25 Zlitos.
I'll take it back for 15 Zlitos, and I think I'm being generous.
Ummm...I'll buy it back for...shall we say 20 Zlitos?
A wizard's diploma costs 40 Zlitos.
A ferry ticket costs 30 Zlitos.
An umbrella costs 35 Zlitos.
A memory viewer costs 30 Zlitos
Hmm.... I'll take your junk for 20 Zlitos.
The price of admission to the casino is 5 Zlitos. Would you like to enter?
Sorry, bud, I don't have none left. I'm waiting for some tanker due in from the island of the Francos. Their refinery produces the gazogem from the gems collected in the under-gas.

The time is near. During the next ceremony, Dark Monk, our reincarnated God, will reunite the four keys of the four Zeelichian races. And the ground will open.. And the gas and its monsters will flee screaming into the sky. And the curse will lift. We will live and die as before, on our Zeelich restored anew.
That's me, what do you want?
Shut up! Are you nuts? Never mention the rebels in public! Meet me in my room, we can talk without danger.
You are lucky to come on behalf of Rick. The government is looking for the dissidents, and you are very rash. What do you want?

I know you. You're Twinsen, the hero of your planet. The Emperor and Dark Monk fear you -- that's why you're a wanted man. The dissidents will help you. Here, take this ring, go to the Twinsunian souvenir shop, and show it to the salesman. He'll take you to them.
So, have you seen the dissidents?
Warning, warning!! Public notice!! Wanted: a Twinsunian named Twinsen, wearing a blue tunic. If you see him, you must immediately inform the police!
Police!!
So! Are you the Twinsunian Johnny told us about?
Listen, Twinsunian. Go to the Mosquibee village in the under-gas. Most of our dissident comrades are already hiding out there. To get in, you have to take the elevator on the platform of the Francos.
Go get a rock-crystal from the Island of Celebration. It'll allow you to operate the laser pistol of Zarnon.
I don't know what to do. The island CX is totally inaccessible. It is impossible to get near it.
You're going to make it twinsunian, I'm sure of that.

Now I understand everything! Dark Monk will explode your planet on the day of his big ceremony. It's the fire from the skies he's always been preaching about. But how can we stop it? Island CX has become a forbidden zone!
Here's the deal. You have to go to the Francos' platform and take the elevator down to the under-gas. Once there, you'll have to find the Mosquibee village.
We have to find a way to go to this island. But how?
Nobody knows for sure. Some guy found that drifting in space. Supposed to come from a very distant garbage can planet...
I've got it! There's a passage between the under-gas and island CX. The entrance is in the Mosquibee village, that's what lets them keep the government soldiers out.

To reach the elevator, you need a powerful weapon. Here, this is a pistolaser of Zarnon. But you will have to find a crystal to make it work. There are some on the side of the volcano of the celebration.
The passage that leaves the Mosquibee village will allow you to reach island CX directly.

From what we know, the passage is blocked by a door. The key belongs to the queen of the mosquibees. It's up to you to convince them of your good faith. But don't forget that our comrades are over there!
No taxi will go there. A guy I knew once tried to get close on a bet. But nobody's seen him since.
I've heard some Zeelichians live under the gas layer. I wonder how you'd get there...

I shouldn't never have watched that commercial for Zeelich, it's so fake. The changing of the guard was lousy, we never even got to see the emperor, and that casino, it's a tourist clip-joint... "Have trust in our friendship..." Hah! Who are they kidding!
Yessir! News steaming hot off the presses!! Latest edition!! Right here, right here!! Plenty for everybody!!
Hey, wait, you're the criminal Twinsunian!! Police!! Police!!
Hello sir!!
Step on in and try your luck. You'll find the best games of chance ever devised. And if you're in luck, you can even try for our Super Jackpot!!! Don't you feel like you're due?? Step right in!!
I come from the under-gas. I took the elevator which goes up to the Francos' platform to come here and witness Dark Monk's ceremony.
You can't climb to the upper city, sir. The elevators are temporarily out of order.
Criminal!!! Help!!!!
No, thanks, go see somebody else! The place is deadly. And today nobody wants to talk about it.
Saw nothing, heard nothing. Now, beat it.
Can't you see I am busy ?
The shows here are truly awful, but they have that certain touch of sleazy slickness, don't you think?
Give us our money back!!!
Brrravo!!!
You can't get in here, it's closed. Members only. Quit loitering now, and get moving.
What are you doing here? You don't belong! now Get out!!
Are you stupid or what? He's right there in front of you!
He's in his room.
Hheeeeee!!!
Get going, mister. You can't stand in the middle -- that'd bother the other pedestrians.
Halt!!!
Hello sir.
Stop!
Welcome to Otringal, sir. Have a pleasant stay.
Stop!!
Halt!!
Careful, sir, you shouldn't run like that. Someone might think you're you know who.
Stop!!
But a thief, of course.
Hello sir.
Stop!!
Hello sir have a pleasant stay among us.
Halt!!
You who are a tourist, you should go to the casino of the gloums. On my behalf.
Murderer!!
Sorry sir, this article is not for sale.
Hello sir. Wouldn't you have an object or something to show me?
Oh, thank you, sir... Police!! Police!!! We got him!!! He's right here!!!
So you got rid of the Emperor. You're a tough guy. Maybe you could soon take his place. You're quite attractive you know.
Hhiiiiiiiii !!!!
